    {
      "id": "trav-impl",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Implementation Glue",
      "position": {
        "x": 1220,
        "y": -40
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Implementation Glue\n\nImplemented now:\n- real document/session navigation commits history only on successful host loads\n- focused-fragment preview stays ephemeral in the address bar\n- replacing the host document resets focus/authority to the new root node\n- `navigate` is now graph-only; it no longer mutates the host graph by creating fallback text nodes from arbitrary URLs\n- script runtime is anchored to the script node's fragment instead of falling back to global focus\n- script event subscriptions and script-node auto-run/execute triggers are gated by the active fragment\n- built-in execution surfaces (`executeNode`, `executeNodes`, interpreter graph execution, API/timer/delay/etc.) now default to active-fragment authority\n- plugin graph reads/writes now follow the active fragment by default\n- plugin selection reads are scoped to the active fragment and plugin-emitted events now carry fragment/plugin provenance while rejecting obvious out-of-scope node targets\n\nFollow-up work:\n- add an explicit import surface if raw text/HTML URL ingestion is still desirable\n- decide how these gates should widen if/when multi-fragment authority domains are introduced",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
